Subject: Re: Dual Port - What does that mean?

The dual port heads were introduced in the 1967 model year in the Type 3s.
That's why your '71 Bus heads have a 311 part number. Some of us Type 3
fans wonder why VW stuck with the single port, single carb configuration
in the Bus for so long.

